belief","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019awiyah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah might forgive any sin except for a man who kills a believer on purpose or a man who dies as an unbeliever.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Nasa\u0304'i\u0304 3984 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14704,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/06\/12\/flee-dajjal-false-messiah\/","url_meta":{"origin":40737,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Dajjal: Run away from the False Messiah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 12, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"'Imran ibn Husayn reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever hears news of the False Messiah, let him flee from him. By Allah, a man will go to him considering himself a believer, but will instead follow him because of doubts he will present.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19079,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/10\/shirk-and-murder\/","url_meta":{"origin":40737,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Shirk: Allah may forgive any sin but idolatry and murder","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 10, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported:\u00a0The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah might forgive any sin except for one who died as an idolater or a believer who killed another believer on purpose.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4270 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064e\u0651\u0631\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2511,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/24\/if-only-knew-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":40737,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hereafter: If people knew what was with Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf the believer knew what was with Allah of punishment, no one would hope for Paradise. If the disbeliever knew what was with Allah of mercy, no one would despair of attaining Paradise.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":39236,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/03\/17\/bribery-kufr-asghar\/","url_meta":{"origin":40737,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Bribery: Taking bribes is an act of lesser unbelief","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 17, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu al-Ahwas reported: Ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said,